{
  format: 1
  name: optional-operand-arithmetic-unspecified
  suite: static
  spec: ["#expressions", "§6.1", "§6.2", "§5.2"]
  tags: ["absence"]
  note: "Spec gap. §6.2 defines 'none' as the absent optional value and §5.2 says a computed expression yielding none is an absent optional, but no rule states how an arithmetic operator treats an optional operand: the checker could reject 'int - int?' as a static type mismatch (CEL static typing, §6.1), or none could propagate making the computed value optional, or absence could act as a zero/identity. Aggregates explicitly skip absent inputs (§7.5) and ordering explicitly places none (Annex B.2) — operators have no such sentence. Load acceptance itself is therefore unpinned."

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.optional@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      items: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        price: "int"
        discount: "int?"
        total: "= .price - .discount"
      }
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: "unspecified"
    violates: ["#expressions"]
    detail: "arithmetic over an optional operand: neither static rejection nor none-propagation is mandated"
  }
}
